track_notes: I started at the Tiger Mine Trailhead to the Arizona Trail and went North.  Plenty of rolling hills and rocks but overall a well-defined trail.  I did this as a trail run.  There are some 4wd road crossings and you could definitely get yourself much closer to the peak, with the right vehicle and planning it would be possible to get within a quarter mile or so of the summit.  The final bushwhack is steep but fairly easy.  Great views from the summit!
